Well, no.

35
00:02:15,130 --> 00:02:16,419
Why do I remember

36
00:02:16,420 --> 00:02:19,570
Zhang Qi's birthday is this weekend?

37
00:02:19,570 --> 00:02:22,089
Why did you all choose to study

38
00:02:22,090 --> 00:02:24,930
instead of having a feast?

39
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,529
She strives for improvement.

40
00:02:27,530 --> 00:02:28,769
Just let her go.

41
00:02:28,770 --> 00:02:31,560
Yes, Sunian is going, too.

42
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:33,470
Is Sunian going, too?

43
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:34,979
Well then. Go ahead.

44
00:02:34,980 --> 00:02:36,579
Study well. Don't go anywhere.

45
00:02:36,580 --> 00:02:38,280
All right.

46
00:02:41,180 --> 00:02:43,900
Essay training camp?

47
00:02:45,330 --> 00:02:48,090
Did the teacher ask you to give a lecture?

48
00:02:49,610 --> 00:02:51,490
I'm going to attend the lecture.

49
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:57,830
Do you even have to attend this?

50
00:02:59,140 --> 00:03:03,080
Well. Try it once in a while.

51
00:03:06,370 --> 00:03:09,110
Great. Go ahead.

52
00:03:13,530 --> 00:03:16,770
Don't you want to check it?

53
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:20,060
Check what?

54
00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:23,779
Zheng, o you want to have a look?

55
00:03:23,779 --> 00:03:25,799
- There's no need.
- Right.

56
00:03:25,799 --> 00:03:27,300
It's nothing.

57
00:03:41,740 --> 00:03:43,259
Let me pour it later.

58
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:44,699
I'd better do something.

59
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:49,210
Or they'll keep saying that I'm lazy.

60
00:03:59,260 --> 00:04:01,360
What's wrong?

61
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:04,000
When I poured the water,

62
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,859
there was a sudden pain here.

63
00:04:05,860 --> 00:04:07,540
My hands slipped.

64
00:04:07,540 --> 00:04:10,180
Does it hurt badly? Where?

65
00:04:11,090 --> 00:04:13,049
I feel better now.

66
00:04:13,050 --> 00:04:14,840
There's nothing.

67
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:17,040
Or we'll take a day off tomorrow

68
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:20,270
and go to the hospital to check.

69
00:04:20,270 --> 00:04:22,819
It's no big deal. Just taking a pill will do.

70
00:04:22,820 --> 00:04:25,810
What's wrong with you?

71
00:04:25,810 --> 00:04:27,769
There's water all above the floor.

72
00:04:27,770 --> 00:04:29,710
I'll clean it up.

73
00:04:29,710 --> 00:04:30,770
I made the mess.

74
00:04:30,771 --> 00:04:32,780
Have a break. Let me clean it up.

75
00:04:32,780 --> 00:04:34,390
Have some warm water later.

76
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:35,981
Come on.

77
00:04:51,260 --> 00:04:53,270
Mom, take your medicine.

78
00:04:53,270 --> 00:04:54,960
Put it there.

79
00:05:02,330 --> 00:05:06,699
Mom, I want to join an essay training course.

80
00:05:06,699 --> 00:05:09,070
It takes two days and one night.

81
00:05:10,020 --> 00:05:11,420
How much is it?

82
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:13,400
It's free.

83
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:17,110
Who will you go with?

84
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:22,530
Shao Xue, Zhang Qi, Lin Shiyin,

85
00:05:24,410 --> 00:05:26,360
and Zheng Sunian.

86
00:05:29,090 --> 00:05:32,620
Mom, I won't go if you don't want me to.

87
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:38,380
Go ahead.

88
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:41,800
It's good to communicate more with friends.

89
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,270
Why are you looking at me?

90
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:45,949
No.

91
00:05:45,949 --> 00:05:49,430
I think you have been in a good mood lately.

92
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:53,479
Did you get used to me being hysterical?

93
00:05:53,479 --> 00:05:57,650
No, it's good this way.

94
00:05:57,650 --> 00:05:59,600
Go and study.

95
00:06:02,460 --> 00:06:04,060
Oh, right.

96
00:06:11,290 --> 00:06:13,090
Eat it.

97
00:06:17,060 --> 00:06:20,529
Today, I wrote a couplet for the nearby store.

98
00:06:20,530 --> 00:06:23,560
They gave me a few packets of sunflower seeds.

99
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:31,810
My hands are always shaky.

100
00:06:31,810 --> 00:06:33,939
I peeled the shells as practice.

101
00:06:33,940 --> 00:06:36,310
So I peeled them for you.

102
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:39,209
Go ahead.

103
00:06:39,210 --> 00:06:42,460
I'll peel some for you when you finish those.

104
00:06:45,580 --> 00:06:47,380
Thank you, Mom.

105
00:06:49,170 --> 00:06:52,360
Mom, remember to take your medicine.

106
00:07:15,330 --> 00:07:17,460
Mom, where's my sun hat?

107
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:19,320
Isn't it there? It's hanging there.

108
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,710
Okay.

109
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:30,479
Mom, where's my woolen coat?

110
00:07:30,479 --> 00:07:32,019
In your closet.

111
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:33,620
Okay.

112
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:40,019
She's just joining an essay training camp.

113
00:07:40,020 --> 00:07:42,820
Why does she bring so many clothes?

114
00:07:42,820 --> 00:07:45,540
She's not going to run away from home, is she?

115
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:48,560
There are five of them together.

116
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:50,700
Don't think too much.

117
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:23,339
<i>[Praising-my-son-one-day ticket]</i>

118
00:08:23,340 --> 00:08:25,889
<i>[One-day-off ticket]</i>

119
00:08:25,890 --> 00:08:26,700
<i>[Traveling-with-my-son ticket]</i>

120
00:08:26,701 --> 00:08:29,010
A leader is deceitful indeed.

121
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:31,550
She cuts corners even when giving a red packet.

122
00:08:31,550 --> 00:08:32,899
Just work hard.

123
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:35,070
I'm going on vacation.

124
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:13,040
Isn't it warm at the beach all year round?

125
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:16,359
This is Northern China. It's not Hainan.

126
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:18,521
It seems I shouldn't have brought my swimming trunks.

127
00:09:18,521 --> 00:09:20,019
Don't mention it.

128
00:09:20,020 --> 00:09:22,660
I regret not bringing my long johns.

129
00:09:22,660 --> 00:09:25,219
At least you wore pants.

130
00:09:25,220 --> 00:09:28,340
I'll catch a cold if it goes on like this.

131
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:32,770
Shall we...

132
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:39,770
Let's go. Goodbye, sea.

133
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:58,670
Are you not feeling well?

134
00:09:59,620 --> 00:10:00,740
It hurts a little.

135
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:05,860
Then go to the hospital this afternoon.

136
00:10:05,860 --> 00:10:09,260
It's okay. I'll just take a break.

137
00:10:09,260 --> 00:10:13,170
You should take care of your body.

138
00:10:15,380 --> 00:10:19,299
Got it, Master. I'll go to the hospital this afternoon.

139
00:10:19,299 --> 00:10:21,720
Let Zheng accompany you.

140
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:25,239
No. All the Restoration Divisions have been busy with the exhibition recently.

141
00:10:25,239 --> 00:10:26,769
His Watchmaker Division will be very busy.

142
00:10:26,770 --> 00:10:29,300
It doesn't matter for a while.

143
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:32,509
I'm okay. It only hurts once in a while.

144
00:10:32,509 --> 00:10:35,699
Okay, Master. I'll go this afternoon.

145
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:44,460
<i>[Golden Beach Grand Hotel]</i>

146
00:10:44,460 --> 00:10:47,550
<i>[Golden Beach Grand Hotel]</i>

147
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:51,500
It's totally different.

148
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,929
Where did you find this place?

149
00:10:53,930 --> 00:10:57,270
One of my followers helped me book it.

150
00:10:57,270 --> 00:11:00,050
No, I have to ask him clearly.

151
00:11:03,260 --> 00:11:07,209
Hello. Didn't you say your uncle owns a five-star hotel?

152
00:11:07,209 --> 00:11:11,879
Qi, you can't even afford a five-star washroom.
<i>[Beijing Qiming High School]</i>

153
00:11:11,879 --> 00:11:15,410
<i>I meant my uncle's hotel</i>

154
00:11:15,410 --> 00:11:17,099
<i>provides five-star services.</i>

155
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:20,430
<i>It'll definitely make you feel... Well.</i>

156
00:11:20,430 --> 00:11:21,900
Make you "feel as if in the freezer."

157
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:23,220
It's "as if feeling at home."
<i>(An idiom)</i>

158
00:11:23,220 --> 00:11:25,350
Don't care about that.

159
00:11:25,350 --> 00:11:27,499
I won't trick you at all.

160
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:30,420
All right. Stop it. Let's hang up.

161
00:11:30,420 --> 00:11:31,880
Did you pay for it?

162
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:33,259
Yes.

163
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:35,850
No way. I'm going to ask for a refund.

164
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:39,000
Let's go.

165
00:11:39,770 --> 00:11:41,270
Let's go.

166
00:11:47,530 --> 00:11:48,899
Refund.

167
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,409
Why?

168
00:11:50,409 --> 00:11:52,500
There's an inconsistency between the image and the actual product.

169
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,899
It's cheating the consumers. We can sue you.

170
00:11:54,899 --> 00:11:57,790
We used to be the same as here before.

171
00:11:57,790 --> 00:12:00,639
But then the management was bad. So we rebuilt it.

172
00:12:00,639 --> 00:12:03,720
But it's all the same inside.

173
00:12:05,510 --> 00:12:07,010
Really?

174
00:12:07,010 --> 00:12:09,019
There's no refund, anyway.

175
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:11,810
- If you cheat us, we'll report you.
- Yes, report you.

176
00:12:11,810 --> 00:12:14,730
Forget it. Let's go up and have a look.

177
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:18,860
Come on.

178
00:12:27,930 --> 00:12:30,770
The boss is terrible at management.

179
00:12:30,770 --> 00:12:32,410
I think it's fine.

180
00:12:32,410 --> 00:12:34,929
Japanese style, quite unique.

181
00:12:34,929 --> 00:12:37,640
It's just that the bed is a little short.

182
00:12:37,690 --> 00:12:41,400
Are the three of you going to sleep on this small bed?

183
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:48,729
Let's go. Let's give them some space.

184
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:59,000
Goodbye.

185
00:13:12,870 --> 00:13:14,670
If I knew Zhang Qi was unreliable,

186
00:13:14,670 --> 00:13:16,720
I'd have booked the rooms.

187
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:19,589
As the old saying goes, the young have to bear hardships.

188
00:13:19,589 --> 00:13:23,329
When my mom first worked, she stayed at the shared house.

189
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:26,300
- Xue.
- What's the matter?

190
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:29,870
Listen. What's that sound?

191
00:13:35,340 --> 00:13:37,700
A mouse!

192
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:40,320
Xue, what's wrong?

193
00:13:44,650 --> 00:13:46,930
There's a mouse!

194
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:57,350
That's the biggest mouse

195
00:13:57,350 --> 00:13:58,859
I've ever seen in my life.

196
00:13:58,860 --> 00:14:00,099
Not really.

197
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:01,720
Then, why did you run?

198
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:04,650
I ran as I saw you all running away.

199
00:14:04,650 --> 00:14:07,649
I won't step inside the room again today.

200
00:14:07,650 --> 00:14:10,260
Then, where are we going to stay tonight?

201
00:14:10,260 --> 00:14:12,789
Let's all stay here tonight. I guess we won't be able to sleep.

202
00:14:12,789 --> 00:14:15,190
It's just right to celebrate Zhang Qi's birthday.

203
00:14:15,190 --> 00:14:17,149
Right, today is your birthday.

204
00:14:17,149 --> 00:14:19,700
That's great. We can eat the cake.

205
00:14:20,550 --> 00:14:25,550
<i>[A9 Clinic]</i>

206
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:27,550
Jin Ning.

207
00:14:27,550 --> 00:14:29,230
Here.

208
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:35,260
Tumour?

209
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:40,400
And there's the possibility of cancer.

210
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:42,870
It needs further examination.

211
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:48,300
How will you examine it?

212
00:14:48,940 --> 00:14:50,220
Undergo magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) first.

213
00:14:50,220 --> 00:14:53,240
Then we can diagnose based on the results.

214
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:56,090
It only hurts once in a while.

215
00:14:56,090 --> 00:14:58,280
It shouldn't be.

216
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:02,179
But only if we diagnose it as soon as possible can we treat it in time.

217
00:15:06,620 --> 00:15:10,310
And of course, don't feel too pressured.

218
00:15:10,310 --> 00:15:11,979
The result isn't out yet, after all.

219
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:13,480
Okay.

220
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:17,099
Thank you, Doctor.

221
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:18,700
It's nothing.

222
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:24,920
<i>[Zhang Qi is one year older]</i>

223
00:15:26,380 --> 00:15:28,270
Blow the candles. Cut the cake.

224
00:15:28,270 --> 00:15:29,600
Hurry up. We haven't had dinner. We're waiting for it.

225
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:32,299
- I haven't made a wish yet.
- Then hurry up.

226
00:15:34,570 --> 00:15:36,140
Why is no one singing?

227
00:15:36,140 --> 00:15:37,979
Ready, go.

228
00:15:37,980 --> 00:15:41,960
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

229
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:42,910
Sing with emotion.

230
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:45,290
Ready, go.

231
00:15:45,290 --> 00:15:52,270
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

232
00:15:52,270 --> 00:15:54,370
One, two, three.

233
00:15:54,370 --> 00:15:56,630
Okay, let's take pictures.

234
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:58,390
Sunian and I first.

235
00:15:58,390 --> 00:15:59,890
Okay.

236
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:07,899
You two are so good-looking. It's like a poster.

237
00:16:07,899 --> 00:16:09,869
Sunian looks like a model.

238
00:16:09,869 --> 00:16:11,470
How about me?

239
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:15,200
You look like the prop beside the model.

240
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,289
Lin Shiyin.

241
00:16:16,290 --> 00:16:18,290
One, two, three.

242
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:21,389
Let's cut the cake first.

243
00:16:21,390 --> 00:16:22,360
- Let's take pictures later.
- Okay.

244
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:24,670
- Come on.
- Cut the cake.

245
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:34,400
<i>[Golden Beach Grand Hotel]</i>

246
00:16:34,435 --> 00:16:35,645
Two Queens.

247
00:16:35,645 --> 00:16:37,004
Does anyone want to follow?

248
00:16:37,005 --> 00:16:39,335
- Does anyone want to follow?
- No.

249
00:16:39,335 --> 00:16:41,343
One pair of two. End game.

250
00:16:41,343 --> 00:16:42,764
My turn.

251
00:16:42,765 --> 00:16:44,575
Four. I have no more cards.

252
00:16:44,575 --> 00:16:46,385
Why do both of you win again?

253
00:16:46,385 --> 00:16:47,474
Do you know why?

254
00:16:47,475 --> 00:16:50,215
Your intelligence determines whether you win or not.

255
00:16:50,215 --> 00:16:52,805
I'm done.

256
00:16:52,805 --> 00:16:55,305
Let's play another game.

257
00:16:56,435 --> 00:16:59,685
Then let's play Truth or Dare.

258
00:17:01,405 --> 00:17:02,644
How to play?

259
00:17:02,645 --> 00:17:04,604
Each person writes down two questions.

260
00:17:04,605 --> 00:17:07,715
Then answer whichever one you draw.

